<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine - Model Years Late 1997 to 2003 - Oil Cooler And Filter - Oil
        Cooler - Cleaning
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="0">
        <title>Cleaning</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To avoid engine damage, should a bearing failure occur, the oil cooler bundle must be replaced
                    because debris from a failed bearing cannot be removed from the cooler bundle.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Immerse oil cooler, front header and filter header in a suitable solvent. Flush and drain
                oil cooler to remove any residue.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Dry all components thoroughly with filtered compressed air.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
